      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here are some of selected shots from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cs22.space/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Prof. Lorie Loeb&amp;rsquo;s modeling class&lt;/a&gt;&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; I took in Fall 22.
Interestingly, I also took &lt;a href=&#34;https://cs87-dartmouth.github.io/Fall2022/darts-overview.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Prof. Wojciech Jarosz&amp;rsquo;s rendering algorithms&lt;/a&gt; in FA22 and they are somewhat complementary to each other.
Rendering Algorithms tells us how to render photorealistic images given the scene and Digital Modeling tells us how to author the scene for a renderer and use the renderer from an artistic perspective.&lt;/p&gt;
